sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant MC as MVNOClient
    participant CF as CorrelationIdFilter
    participant SF as SecurityFilter
    participant TF as TenantIsolationFilter
    participant DC as DeviceDetailsController
    participant DS as DeviceDetailsService
    participant VC as VendorClient
    participant VB as VendorBackend
    participant AL as AuditLogService

    MC->>CF: GET /api/v1/devices?msisdn=+14155551234&mvno=acme-mobile
    CF->>CF: Extract or generate X-Correlation-Id (UUID)
    CF->>SF: forward with correlationId in MDC

    SF->>SF: Validate API Key / JWT bearer token
    SF->>TF: forward (auth resolved: mvno=acme-mobile)

    TF->>TF: Assert request.mvno == authenticated.mvno
    TF->>DC: forward (tenant validated)

    DC->>DS: queryDevice(msisdn, mvno, correlationId)

    Note over VC,VB: Attempt 1 of 3
    DS->>VC: fetchDeviceDetails(msisdn, correlationId)
    VC->>VB: GET /vendor/devices?msisdn=+14155551234
    VB-->>VC: 503 Service Unavailable (or timeout)
    VC->>VC: Resilience4j: record failure, schedule retry (backoff 500ms)

    Note over VC,VB: Attempt 2 of 3 (backoff 500ms)
    VC->>VB: GET /vendor/devices?msisdn=+14155551234
    VB-->>VC: 503 Service Unavailable
    VC->>VC: Resilience4j: record failure, schedule retry (backoff 1000ms)

    Note over VC,VB: Attempt 3 of 3 (backoff 1000ms)
    VC->>VB: GET /vendor/devices?msisdn=+14155551234
    VB-->>VC: 503 Service Unavailable
    VC->>VC: Resilience4j: failure rate >= threshold → CircuitBreaker OPENS

    VC-->>DS: throw VendorUnavailableException
    DS-->>DC: propagate VendorUnavailableException

    DC->>AL: auditLog(correlationId, msisdn_masked, mvno, 503, VENDOR_ERROR, durationMs)
    AL-->>DC: logged (async, non-blocking)

    DC-->>MC: HTTP 503 {"errorCode":"VENDOR_UNAVAILABLE","message":"Device vendor is temporarily unavailable. Please retry later.","correlationId":"<uuid>"}
    Note right of MC: X-Correlation-Id header included in response

    Note over VC,VB: Subsequent requests fast-fail while CircuitBreaker is OPEN (30s default)
